subSubSection.paragraph:
Collum oval. Metatergal macrochaetae short and clavate, tegument deeply alveolate with uneven and curved edges, as well as with longitudinal, low and short crests scattered all over (
Figs 19, 20
). One legless body segment in front of telson, all setae on the latter pointed. Spinnerets devoid of apical setae (apparently, broken off), rod-like.

